    • Method Detail

      • random

        public static <T> T random(Type type,
                           Object... info)
                    throws IllegalArgumentException
        Creates a random instance of the class provided, if a suitable RandomGenerator is registered. A suitable generator can be registered in several ways:
      • automatically when placed in same package as the SupportedType
      • Manually by registering either class or instance directly to addRandomGenerator(com.namics.commons.random.generator.RandomGenerator)
      • Manually by registering package for scanning to addRandomGenerators(String)
Parameters:
type - class to create a random object for.
info - optional additional information for the object to create, e.g. a field name.
Returns:
Random instance of the class.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if no suitable RandomGenerator is registered.

  • random

    public static <T> T random(Class<T> clazz,
                           Object... info)
                    throws IllegalArgumentException
    Creates a random instance of the class provided, if a suitable RandomGenerator is registered. A suitable generator can be registered in several ways:
  • automatically when placed in same package as the SupportedType
  • Manually by registering either class or instance directly to addRandomGenerator(com.namics.commons.random.generator.RandomGenerator)
  • Manually by registering package for scanning to addRandomGenerators(String)
Parameters:
clazz - class to create a random object for.
info -
Returns:
Random instance of the class.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if no suitable RandomGenerator is registered.

  • populateBean

    public static <T> T populateBean(T bean)
    Populates a bean instance with random values for properties of a supported types of RandomGenerators.
    Type Parameters:
    T - Type of the bean to be populated
    Parameters:
    bean - bean to be populated
    Returns:
    populated bean, the original object is populated, so the returned object is the same instance as provided as parameter.
    See Also:
    RandomGenerator, random(Class, Object...)
